Princess Mary shuddered; her nurse, putting down the stock- ing she was knitting, went to the window and leaning out tried to catch the open casement. The cold wind flapped the ends of her ker- chief and her loose locks of gray hair. 
"Princess, my dear, there's someone driving up the avenue!" she said, holding the casement and not closing it. "With lanterns. Most likely the doctor."
